      • checkTableName

        public boolean checkTableName(java.lang.String name)
        Checks if the name provided is already in use by some other table in the document or not. Performs a case insensitive search on the table column name.
        Parameters:
        name - String the name of the table to checked for availability.
        Returns:
        boolean, true if the provided name is not taken by any other existing table, false otherwise.

      • checkTableName

        public boolean checkTableName(java.lang.String name,
                     java.lang.String identifier)
        Checks if the name provided is already in use by some other table in the document or not except for the table with given identifier. Performs a case insensitive search on the table column name.
        Parameters:
        name - String the name of the table to checked for availability.
        Returns:
        boolean, true if the provided name is not taken by any other existing table, false otherwise.
